Les plus classiques ce sont les pommes de terre, les carottes, les poireaux, les haricots, les flageolets, la salade, les tomates, les aubergines, les cucurbitacées sont revenues à la mode : potimarron, courgette. Il faut un petit coin pour le persil, le thym, le romarin, le laurier sauce.
Pour les fruits, les pommes, poires et surtout cerises.
Le jardin individuel est une institution en France car il permettait aux foyers à faible revenu d'avoir une source de nourriture presque gratuite. D'où les "jardins ouvriers", de petits lopins de terre que les entreprises industrielles mettaient à disposition des ouvriers.

Choosing the right bike can be a daunting task, especially if you're planning to spend a significant amount of money. Here are a few things to consider when choosing a bike:

Purpose: Consider what you will be using the bike for. Are you planning to use it for commuting, road riding, off-road riding, or a combination of all these? Different bikes are designed for different purposes, and it's important to choose one that is best suited to your needs.

Size and fit: Make sure to choose a bike that is the right size for you. A bike that is too small or too large can be uncomfortable and can negatively impact your performance.

Budget: Consider your budget when choosing a bike. If you're planning to spend 1k euro on a bike, you may be able to find a high-quality road or mountain bike, or even a hybrid bike that combines elements of both.

Brand and model: Research the different brands and models of bikes that are available in your price range. Look at customer reviews and ratings, and consider factors such as durability, weight, and component quality.

Test ride: Before making a final decision, it's important to test ride the bike to see how it feels and handles. This will help you to get a better sense of how the bike performs and whether it's the right fit for you.

It's also important to keep in mind that cycling is a diverse sport and you can have different bikes for different activities. You can have a road bike for long distance and fast rides, a mountain bike for off-road adventures and a city bike for your daily commute.

It's always a good idea to consult with a professional bike-fitter or a bike shop to get the right advice and recommendations for your specific needs and riding style.

日本語わ、スベテの 音ヨミを 漢字で、スベテの 訓ヨミを カナで カク 必要が アル。 コレわ 韓國語の 正書法に ニテイマス。
ひらがなわ 女性の 文字で アリ、助詞の、を、わ (は)、で、へ ナドに 使用デキル。西洋言語からの 借用語で サエ アル カモシレマセン (キョウの カタカナの 反對)。
ヒトナマエにわ タマシイが 必要なので、人名や 地名にわ 漢字を 使用デキマス。
マタ、日本語わ 新字體の 使用を ヤメ、傳統的な 文字を 使用スル 必要が アル。
單語の マに すぺーすを 使用スル 必要が アル。
コレに ヨリ、日本語の 正書法の 一貫性が タカマリマス。

>選擇2:
日本語わ、第二次世界大戰前の 正書法と 同樣に、舊字體と カタカナで 書ク 必要が 有ル。
ひらがなわ、助詞と 西洋の 外來語を 表ス タメに 使用デキル (今日の カタカナの 反對)。
單語の 間に すぺーすを 使用スル 必要が 有ル。
助詞「は」、「わ」書ク。

Welcome to /flag/ + /extraflags/, a lovely general for users to discuss flags, Extra Flags, and autistic activities while funposting.

>What is Extra Flags?
Extra Flags is an open-source userscript that lets you choose regional flags, like states and provinces, to add the already existing national flags on /int/, /pol/, /sp/, and /bant/.

Instructions and video guides for installing Extra Flags can be found here: https://flagtism.gitlab.io/Extra-Flags-for-4chan/
Requests to add or change flags can be made here: https://gitlab.com/flagtism/Extra-Flags-for-4chan/-/issues

>Collecting flags?
>Filling maps?
World template: https://gitlab.com/flagtism/Extra-Flags-for-4chan/tree/master/maps/World.png (embed)
Extra Flags templates: https://gitlab.com/flagtism/Extra-Flags-for-4chan/tree/master/maps
Labelled Extra Flag templates: https://imgur.com/a/J9CDp54

>Flag Informations
About 4chan flags: https://i.imgur.com/w9VDsop.png
Flag creation guide: https://i.imgur.com/GLnizJD.png

>Tools
FlagHunter: https://whatisthisimnotgoodwithcomputers.com/#!/flaghunter
Flaggot: https://github.com/dnsev/flaggot
Flag Fixer: https://github.com/ebinBuddha/4chan-Flag-Fixer
Extra Flag Lister: https://github.com/ebinBuddha/Flag-Lister-for-4chan
More tools: https://nun.wtf/extraflags.html
